# Component Patterns

## Page Component Template

```tsx
import { Typography } from "antd";
import { useTranslation } from "react-i18next";
import styles from "./MyPage.module.css";

const { Title, Paragraph } = Typography;

export const MyPage: React.FC = () => {
  const { t } = useTranslation();

  return (
    <div className={styles.container}>
      <Title level={1}>{t("section.title")}</Title>
      <Paragraph type="secondary">{t("section.text")}</Paragraph>
    </div>
  );
};
```

## Rules

- One component per file, file name matches component name
- Pages in `src/pages/FeatureName/FeatureNamePage.tsx` with co-located `.module.css`
- Shared components in `src/components/ComponentName/ComponentName.tsx`
- Use antd `Typography`, `Flex`, `Space` instead of raw HTML + custom CSS
- Use antd `Table` with `scroll={{ x: number }}` for responsive admin tables
- Use antd `Form` with `layout="vertical"` for forms
- Destructure antd sub-components at module level: `const { Title } = Typography;`
- Use `formatPrice(amount, currency, i18n.language)` for locale-aware prices
